  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="shortdesc:1;23:14">Run <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:26">md-validate validate</codeph> with a directory path to
  validate all Markdown files in that directory and its subdirectories at once.
  Use this before a release or periodic quality review.</shortdesc>

  <taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="taskbody:1;27:13">

    <prereq id="prereq" class="- topic/section task/prereq " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="prereq:1;29:25">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:1;30:10">markdown-validator is installed and the virtual environment is active.
      See <xref href="t_install.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="xref:1;31:40" type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>Install markdown-validator<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Install markdown-validator with pip in a Python virtual environment.   After installation, the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_install.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;24:35">md-validate</codeph> command is available from   your terminal.</desc></xref>.</p>
    </prereq>

    <context id="context" class="- topic/section task/context " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="context:1;34:27">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:2;35:10">When you pass a directory path instead of a file path, markdown-validator
      scans every <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="filepath:1;36:29">.md</filepath> file in that directory recursively.
      It produces one report per file and a summary in the terminal.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:3;38:10">A single failing file sets the exit code to <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:2;38:62">1</codeph> for the
      entire run. This is the behavior CI pipelines rely on to gate the merge.</p>
    </context>

    <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="steps:1;42:12">

      <step id="step-run-dir" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="step:1;44:31">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="cmd:1;45:14">Run the validate command with a directory path.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="info:1;46:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;47:43">md-validate validate docs/ --rules rules/tutorial.json</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:4;48:14">Replace <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:3;48:30">docs/</codeph> with the path to the directory you
          want to scan and <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:4;49:36">rules/tutorial.json</codeph> with your team's
          rule set.</p>
        </info>
        <stepresult class="- topic/itemgroup task/stepresult " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="stepresult:1;52:21">The tool prints a report for each file it validates, followed
        by a summary of how many files passed and failed.</stepresult>
      </step>

      <step id="step-review-summary" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="step:2;56:38">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="cmd:2;57:14">Review the summary at the end of the output.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="info:2;58:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;59:43">Summary: 47 files validated — 45 passed, 2 failed</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:5;60:14">Scroll up to find the per-file reports for the two failed files. The
          file path is shown at the top of each report.</p>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-save" importance="optional" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="step:3;65:50">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="cmd:3;66:14">To save per-file reports, add the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:5;66:56">--output</codeph>
        option.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="info:3;68:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeblock:3;69:43">md-validate validate docs/ --rules rules/tutorial.json --output reports/</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:6;70:14">The tool creates one report file per validated Markdown file in the
          <filepath class="+ topic/ph sw-d/filepath " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="filepath:2;71:21">reports/</filepath> directory. This is useful for sharing
          results with your team or tracking quality over time. For more about
          saving reports, see <xref href="t_save-reports.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="xref:2;73:64" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Save validation reports to a directory<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_save-reports.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:30">--output</codeph> option to write one report file   per validated document to a directory. This is useful for sharing results with   your team, uploading reports as CI artifacts, or tracking quality over time.</desc></xref>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>

    </steps>

    <result id="result" class="- topic/section task/result " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="result:1;79:25">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="p:7;80:10">Every Markdown file in the directory has been validated. Files with
      Required failures are identified in the terminal output and, if you used
      <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_validate-directory.dita" xtrc="codeph:6;82:15">--output</codeph>, in the saved report files.</p>
    </result>

